values.name: recognition_01
values.description: The default recognition model for "Detect". All those faceIds created before 2019 March are bonded with this recognition model.

values.name: recognition_04
values.description: Recognition model released in 2021 February. It's recommended to use this recognition model for better recognition accuracy.

Enums.description: The recognition model for the face.

Enums.description: The status of long running operation.

Enums.name: FaceDetectionModel

values.name: detection_01
values.description: The default detection model. Recommend for near frontal face detection. For scenarios with exceptionally large angle (head-pose) faces, occluded faces or wrong image orientation, the faces in such cases may not be detected.

values.name: detection_02
values.description: Detection model released in 2019 May with improved accuracy especially on small, side and blurry faces.

values.name: detection_03
values.description: Detection model released in 2021 February with improved accuracy especially on small faces.

Enums.description: The detection model for the face.

Enums.name: Versions
Enums.description: API versions for Azure AI Face API.

Enums.name: FaceAttributeType

values.name: occlusion
values.description: Whether each facial area is occluded, including forehead, eyes and mouth.

values.name: accessories
values.description: Accessories around face, including 'headwear', 'glasses' and 'mask'. Empty array means no accessories detected. Note this is after a face is detected. Large mask could result in no face to be detected.

values.name: blur
values.description: Face is blurry or not. Level returns 'Low', 'Medium' or 'High'. Value returns a number between [0,1], the larger the blurrier.

values.name: exposure
values.description: Face exposure level. Level returns 'GoodExposure', 'OverExposure' or 'UnderExposure'.

values.name: noise
values.description: Noise level of face pixels. Level returns 'Low', 'Medium' and 'High'. Value returns a number between [0,1], the larger the noisier

values.name: mask
values.description: Whether each face is wearing a mask. Mask type returns 'noMask', 'faceMask', 'otherMaskOrOcclusion', or 'uncertain'. Value returns a boolean 'noseAndMouthCovered' indicating whether nose and mouth are covered.

values.name: qualityForRecognition
values.description: The overall image quality regarding whether the image being used in the detection is of sufficient quality to attempt face recognition on. The value is an informal rating of low, medium, or high. Only 'high' quality images are recommended for person enrollment and quality at or above 'medium' is recommended for identification scenarios. The attribute is only available when using recognition models recognition_03 or recognition_04.

Enums.description: Available options for detect face with attribute.

values.name: otherMaskOrOcclusion
values.description: Other types of mask or occlusion.

Enums.name: QualityForRecognition
Enums.description: Indicates quality of image for recognition.

Enums.name: LivenessOperationMode

values.name: Passive
values.description: Utilizes a passive liveness technique that requires no additional actions from the user. Requires normal indoor lighting and high screen brightness for optimal performance. And thus, this mode has a narrow operational envelope and will not be suitable for scenarios that requires the end-user's to be in bright lighting conditions. Note: this is the only supported mode for the Mobile (iOS and Android) solution.

values.name: PassiveActive
values.description: This mode utilizes a hybrid passive or active liveness technique that necessitates user cooperation. It is optimized to require active motion only under suboptimal lighting conditions. Unlike the passive mode, this mode has no lighting restrictions, and thus offering a broader operational envelope. This mode is preferable on Web based solutions due to the lack of automatic screen brightness control available on browsers which hinders the Passive mode's operational envelope on Web based solutions.

Enums.description: The liveness operation mode to drive the client's end-user experience.

Operations.Name: detectFromUrlImpl
Operations.Summary: Detect human faces in an image, return face rectangles, and optionally with faceIds, landmarks, and attributes.
Operations.Description: Please refer to https://learn.microsoft.com/rest/api/face/face-detection-operations/detect-from-url for more details.

Parameters.Name: contentType
Parameters.Description: The format of the HTTP payload.

Parameters.Name: detectionModel
Parameters.Description: The 'detectionModel' associated with the detected faceIds. Supported 'detectionModel' values include 'detection_01', 'detection_02' and 'detection_03'. The default value is 'detection_01'. 'detection_03' is recommended since its accuracy is improved on smaller faces (64x64 pixels) and rotated face orientations.

Parameters.Name: recognitionModel
Parameters.Description: The 'recognitionModel' associated with the detected faceIds. Supported 'recognitionModel' values include 'recognition_01', 'recognition_02', 'recognition_03' or 'recognition_04'. The default value is 'recognition_01'. 'recognition_04' is recommended since its accuracy is improved on faces wearing masks compared with 'recognition_03', and its overall accuracy is improved compared with 'recognition_01' and 'recognition_02'.

Parameters.Name: returnFaceId
Parameters.Description: Return faceIds of the detected faces or not. The default value is true.

Parameters.Name: returnFaceAttributes
Parameters.Description: Analyze and return the one or more specified face attributes in the comma-separated string like 'returnFaceAttributes=headPose,glasses'. Face attribute analysis has additional computational and time cost.

Parameters.Name: returnFaceLandmarks
Parameters.Description: Return face landmarks of the detected faces or not. The default value is false.

Parameters.Name: returnRecognitionModel
Parameters.Description: Return 'recognitionModel' or not. The default value is false. This is only applicable when returnFaceId = true.

Parameters.Name: faceIdTimeToLive
Parameters.Description: The number of seconds for the face ID being cached. Supported range from 60 seconds up to 86400 seconds. The default value is 86400 (24 hours).

Operations.Name: detectFromSessionImage
Operations.Summary: Detect human faces in an image, return face rectangles, and optionally with faceIds, landmarks, and attributes.
Operations.Description: Please refer to https://learn.microsoft.com/rest/api/face/face-detection-operations/detect-from-session-image-id for more details.

Parameters.Name: contentType
Parameters.Description: The format of the HTTP payload.

Parameters.Name: detectionModel
Parameters.Description: The 'detectionModel' associated with the detected faceIds. Supported 'detectionModel' values include 'detection_01', 'detection_02' and 'detection_03'. The default value is 'detection_01'. 'detection_03' is recommended since its accuracy is improved on smaller faces (64x64 pixels) and rotated face orientations.

Parameters.Name: recognitionModel
Parameters.Description: The 'recognitionModel' associated with the detected faceIds. Supported 'recognitionModel' values include 'recognition_01', 'recognition_02', 'recognition_03' or 'recognition_04'. The default value is 'recognition_01'. 'recognition_04' is recommended since its accuracy is improved on faces wearing masks compared with 'recognition_03', and its overall accuracy is improved compared with 'recognition_01' and 'recognition_02'.

Parameters.Name: returnFaceId
Parameters.Description: Return faceIds of the detected faces or not. The default value is true.

Parameters.Name: returnFaceAttributes
Parameters.Description: Analyze and return the one or more specified face attributes in the comma-separated string like 'returnFaceAttributes=headPose,glasses'. Face attribute analysis has additional computational and time cost.

Parameters.Name: returnFaceLandmarks
Parameters.Description: Return face landmarks of the detected faces or not. The default value is false.

Parameters.Name: returnRecognitionModel
Parameters.Description: Return 'recognitionModel' or not. The default value is false. This is only applicable when returnFaceId = true.

Parameters.Name: faceIdTimeToLive
Parameters.Description: The number of seconds for the face ID being cached. Supported range from 60 seconds up to 86400 seconds. The default value is 86400 (24 hours).
